    <div class="rulebook-container">
        <h2>Club Guidelines and Policies</h2>
        <p>Our goal is to foster a collaborative and competitive environment where members can grow as coders, problem solvers, and critical thinkers. To ensure fairness, consistency, and respect within the club, we have outlined the following rules. Please read them carefully.</p>

        <ul class="rulebook">
            <li><strong>1. Attendance Policy</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Session Frequency:</strong> The club conducts a minimum of 5 sessions per week, each lasting no more than 2 hours.</li>
                    <li><strong>Attendance Requirement:</strong> Members are expected to attend at least 3 out of the 5 sessions each week.</li>
                    <li><strong>Non-Compliance:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>A warning call will be issued if a member fails to meet the attendance requirement.</li>
                            <li>Repeated non-compliance may lead to a review of your membership status in the club.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>

            <li><strong>2. Membership Criteria</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Entrance Contest: </strong>Each semester, the club will host an entrance contest to recruit new members.</li>
                    <li><strong>Selection Process:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Top performers from the contest will be shortlisted.</li>
                            <li>Shortlisted candidates will participate in a light interview round to finalize membership.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>

            <li><strong>3. Plagiarism and Cheating</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Monitoring: </strong>A dedicated judging team will evaluate all contest submissions and activities on recommended platforms.</li>
                    <li><strong>Consequences for Cheating</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>A red flag added to your user ID on the club website, permanently marking you as a cheater.</li>
                            <li>If found cheating, you may receive up to one warning call before membership termination.</li>
                            <li>Subsequent incidents will result in Immediate termination of membership.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Note:</h3>
        <p>We believe in maintaining the integrity and reputation of the club. Abiding by these rules ensures a fair and productive environment for all members. If you have questions or concerns, feel free to reach out to the club leadership team.</p>

    </div>
</div>
